          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em>predecessor</html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is a top element of its
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FL/" title="The strict downset sieve of a direct category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FL/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FL/" type="local">strict downset</fr:link>: a strict morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho  : p \to  x]]></fr:tex>
through which every strict morphism into <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> factors uniquely.
Equivalently, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {StrictDown}{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}} \cong  \mathsf {y}\, p]]></fr:tex> — the downset is representable.</html:p>
            <html:p>The Yoneda lemma then collapses <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" title="Later on presheaves" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" type="local">later</fr:link> to evaluation:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\rhd  P\,{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}
   = \mathsf {Psh}\,\mathcal {C}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {StrictDown}{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}},\, P\right )\mathclose {}}
   \cong  \mathsf {Psh}\,\mathcal {C}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {y}\, p,\, P\right )\mathclose {}}
   \cong  P{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {next}]]></fr:tex> becoming restriction along <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho ]]></fr:tex>. The name is from the
naturals: every strict map into <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex> factors through
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \to  n+1]]></fr:tex>, so on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\omega ]]></fr:tex> — the
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G6/" title="Streams in the topos of trees" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G6/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G6/" type="local">topos of trees</fr:link> — later is just the shift
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\rhd  P\,{\mathopen {}\left (0\right )\mathclose {}} \cong  \top ,
   \qquad 
   \rhd  P\,{\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}} \cong  P{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
and a <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" title="Löb induction for presheaves on a direct category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" type="local">Löb</fr:link> step is a base value together with a rule
producing the value at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex> from the value at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>When this predecessor exists, we can give a simpler description of
later, as in the topos of trees, but this may not be possible in all
direct categories.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
