        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/" type="external">https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00GE/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00GE/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00GE/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Fixed points of locally contractive functors are unique">Fixed points of locally contractive functors are unique</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> endofunctor on
presheaves over a <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" title="Direct categories" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" type="local">direct category</fr:link>, and suppose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is
<html:em>any</html:em> fixed point of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>: an object with an isomorphism
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha  : F X \cong  X]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (X, \alpha \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is an
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F8/" title="Initial algebra" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F8/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F8/" type="local">initial algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu  F]]></fr:tex>, and simultaneously
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (X, \alpha ^{-1}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FA/" title="Terminal coalgebra" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FA/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FA/" type="local">terminal coalgebra</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\nu  F]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Both claims follow from
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">every value of the hylomorphism profunctor being a singleton</fr:link>.
For initiality of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (X, \alpha \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>: a map to an algebra
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (B, \beta \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> satisfying the initiality square is the same thing
as a <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FT/" title="Hylomorphisms" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FT/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FT/" type="local">hylomorphism</fr:link> from the coalgebra
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (X, \alpha ^{-1}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (B, \beta \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and there is exactly one
of those. Terminality follows similarly.</html:p>
            <html:p>Thus for locally contractive <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>, we have an inital-final coincidence
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mu  F \;\cong \; \nu  F,]]></fr:tex>
and guarded domain equations have <html:em>unique</html:em> solutions.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/" type="external">https://stevenschaefer.net/stevenschaefer/</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive">Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is a
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> endofunctor on presheaves over a
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" title="Direct categories" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" type="local">direct category</fr:link>, then every value of the
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FV/" title="The coalgebra-to-algebra profunctor" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FV/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FV/" type="local">profunctor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Hylo}]]></fr:tex> is a singleton: every coalgebra is
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" title="Recursive coalgebras and corecursive algebras" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FU/" type="local">recursive</fr:link> and every algebra is corecursive.</html:p>
            <html:p>The proof is one application of <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" title="Löb induction for presheaves on a direct category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" type="local">Löb</fr:link>. A hylomorphism from
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> is a fixed point of
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[h \mapsto  c \star  F h \star  \alpha ]]></fr:tex>
on the presheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \Rightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> of morphisms. Local contractivity
factors this assignment through <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rhd {\mathopen {}\left (X \Rightarrow  B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, so Löb
provides a fixed point and provides it uniquely.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
