            <fr:title text="Locally contractive endofunctors">Locally contractive endofunctors</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \Rightarrow  Y]]></fr:tex> for the presheaf of morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \to  Y]]></fr:tex>.
An endofunctor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on presheaves is <html:em>locally contractive</html:em> when its
action on morphisms factors through <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" title="Later on presheaves" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FN/" type="local">later</fr:link>: there is a map
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[F_\delta  : \rhd {\mathopen {}\left (X \Rightarrow  Y\right )\mathclose {}} \to 
   {\mathopen {}\left (F X \Rightarrow  F Y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex></html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
